===Climate===
According to the [[Köppen climate classification]] system, Hartsel has a Cold [[Semi-arid climate]] (''BSk''). According to the [[United States Department of Agriculture]], the Plant [[Hardiness zone]] is 3b with an average annual extreme minimum temperature of {{convert|−30.7|°F}}.<ref name="USDA">{{cite web|url=https://planthardiness.ars.usda.gov/|publisher=[[United States Department of Agriculture]]|access-date=2019-07-11|title=USDA Interactive Plant Hardiness Map}}</ref>

Summers are warm with chilly nights in the 30s and 40s (°F) and some thunderstorm activity during the months of July and August. Winters are cold and dry with lows below zero.<ref>{{Cite web|title=National Weather Service Climate|url=https://w2.weather.gov/climate/xmacis.php?wfo=bou|last=Team|first=National Weather Service Corporate Image Web|website=w2.weather.gov|language=EN-US|access-date=2020-05-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=HARTSEL, COLORADO - Climate Summary|url=https://wrcc.dri.edu/cgi-bin/cliMAIN.pl?cohart|website=wrcc.dri.edu|access-date=2020-05-29}}</ref>  A climate writeup consisting of [[interpolated]] data is below.

